The Linear MCP server is a standardized interface that allows AI agents and models to interact with Linear data, including issues, projects, teams, and comments [1][2][3]. Official support is provided via a centrally hosted, authenticated remote MCP server at https://mcp.linear.app/mcp [1].

You can integrate this server using the following configuration in your MCP settings [1]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "linear": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote", "https://mcp.linear.app/mcp"]
    }
  }
}
```

The server supports Streamable HTTP and authenticated API access via `Authorization: Bearer` headers [1][4]. Numerous open-source, TypeScript-based implementations also exist via npm [5][4][2][3].
